<subSubSection box="[199,1256,468,492]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1438,256,1126]" box="[199,1256,468,492]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,468,492]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhang &amp; Maddison" authorityYear="2012" box="[406,495,468,492]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bathippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="directus">
<emphasis box="[406,495,468,492]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">directus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, referring to the male chelicerae projecting almost straight forward.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1438,256,1126]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,503,528]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Differs from other species by the presence of two cusps near the base of the male cheliceral fang (
<figureCitation box="[159,287,538,562]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–14" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1424,205,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-94@6.[151,1436,195,1861]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 5–14. Bathippus directus sp. nov. 5 male paratype, dorsal view; 6 female paratype, dorsal view; 7 male left palp, ventral view; 8 male left palp, retrolateral view; 9 male left palp (with patella and femur), retrolateral view; 10 male left chelicera, retrolateral view; 11 male left chelicera, prolateral view; 12 female left chelicera, back view; 13 epigynum, ventral view; 14 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–6, 2.0 mm; 7–12, 0.2 mm; 13–14, 0.1 mm." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs 10–11</figureCitation>
), the long embolus and the abruptly narrowed distal end of the retrolateral tibial apophysis of the male palp (
<figureCitation box="[214,315,574,598]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–14" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1424,205,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-94@6.[151,1436,195,1861]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 5–14. Bathippus directus sp. nov. 5 male paratype, dorsal view; 6 female paratype, dorsal view; 7 male left palp, ventral view; 8 male left palp, retrolateral view; 9 male left palp (with patella and femur), retrolateral view; 10 male left chelicera, retrolateral view; 11 male left chelicera, prolateral view; 12 female left chelicera, back view; 13 epigynum, ventral view; 14 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–6, 2.0 mm; 7–12, 0.2 mm; 13–14, 0.1 mm." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs 7–9</figureCitation>
), the large window of the epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[734,816,574,598]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–14" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1424,205,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-94@6.[151,1436,195,1861]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 5–14. Bathippus directus sp. nov. 5 male paratype, dorsal view; 6 female paratype, dorsal view; 7 male left palp, ventral view; 8 male left palp, retrolateral view; 9 male left palp (with patella and femur), retrolateral view; 10 male left chelicera, retrolateral view; 11 male left chelicera, prolateral view; 12 female left chelicera, back view; 13 epigynum, ventral view; 14 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–6, 2.0 mm; 7–12, 0.2 mm; 13–14, 0.1 mm." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
), and the large and spherical spermathecae of the vulva (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,609,633]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–14" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1424,205,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-94@6.[151,1436,195,1861]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 5–14. Bathippus directus sp. nov. 5 male paratype, dorsal view; 6 female paratype, dorsal view; 7 male left palp, ventral view; 8 male left palp, retrolateral view; 9 male left palp (with patella and femur), retrolateral view; 10 male left chelicera, retrolateral view; 11 male left chelicera, prolateral view; 12 female left chelicera, back view; 13 epigynum, ventral view; 14 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–6, 2.0 mm; 7–12, 0.2 mm; 13–14, 0.1 mm." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Female genitalia resembles that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Zabka, 1981" authorityName="Zabka" authorityYear="1981" box="[654,968,604,633]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Euophrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="evae">
<emphasis box="[654,819,609,633]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Euophrys evae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zabka, M." box="[826,968,604,633]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="407 - 413" refId="ref31269" refString="Zabka, M. (1981) Salticidae from Kashmir and Ladakh (Arachnida, Araneae). Senckenbergiana Biologica, 61, 407 - 413." type="journal article" year="1981">Żabka, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the narrower copulatory duct and the larger spermatheca of the vulva (
<figureCitation box="[789,872,644,668]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–14" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1424,205,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-94@6.[151,1436,195,1861]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 5–14. Bathippus directus sp. nov. 5 male paratype, dorsal view; 6 female paratype, dorsal view; 7 male left palp, ventral view; 8 male left palp, retrolateral view; 9 male left palp (with patella and femur), retrolateral view; 10 male left chelicera, retrolateral view; 11 male left chelicera, prolateral view; 12 female left chelicera, back view; 13 epigynum, ventral view; 14 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–6, 2.0 mm; 7–12, 0.2 mm; 13–14, 0.1 mm." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1438,256,1126]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,344,679,704]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[353,410,679,703]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[427,529,679,703]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">holotype</typeStatus>
, UBC-SEM AR00077). Carapace length 3.6 (variation 3.5–3.8, n=6); abdomen length 5.0. Chelicera (
<figureCitation box="[398,528,714,738]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–14" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1424,205,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-94@6.[151,1436,195,1861]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 5–14. Bathippus directus sp. nov. 5 male paratype, dorsal view; 6 female paratype, dorsal view; 7 male left palp, ventral view; 8 male left palp, retrolateral view; 9 male left palp (with patella and femur), retrolateral view; 10 male left chelicera, retrolateral view; 11 male left chelicera, prolateral view; 12 female left chelicera, back view; 13 epigynum, ventral view; 14 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–6, 2.0 mm; 7–12, 0.2 mm; 13–14, 0.1 mm." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs 10–11</figureCitation>
): dark red brown; elongate and extending forward; promargin with four teeth and retromargin with one big tooth; fang with two cusps near the base. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[964,1067,750,774]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–14" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1424,205,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-94@6.[151,1436,195,1861]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 5–14. Bathippus directus sp. nov. 5 male paratype, dorsal view; 6 female paratype, dorsal view; 7 male left palp, ventral view; 8 male left palp, retrolateral view; 9 male left palp (with patella and femur), retrolateral view; 10 male left chelicera, retrolateral view; 11 male left chelicera, prolateral view; 12 female left chelicera, back view; 13 epigynum, ventral view; 14 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–6, 2.0 mm; 7–12, 0.2 mm; 13–14, 0.1 mm." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Figs 7–9</figureCitation>
): sandy yellow. Retrolateral loop of sperm duct wide, occuping about three quaters of the bulb width. Embolus coiled for about half a circle. Retrolateral tibial apophysis thick proximally and narrowed abruptly near distal end. Measurements of legs: I 13.7, II 9.0, III 10.7, IV 9.3. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation box="[617,687,855,879]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–14" captionStartId="6.[151,263,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1424,205,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-94@6.[151,1436,195,1861]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 5–14. Bathippus directus sp. nov. 5 male paratype, dorsal view; 6 female paratype, dorsal view; 7 male left palp, ventral view; 8 male left palp, retrolateral view; 9 male left palp (with patella and femur), retrolateral view; 10 male left chelicera, retrolateral view; 11 male left chelicera, prolateral view; 12 female left chelicera, back view; 13 epigynum, ventral view; 14 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 5–6, 2.0 mm; 7–12, 0.2 mm; 13–14, 0.1 mm." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
): carapace yellow orange with indistinct gray markings; abdomen gray brown, with yellow orange speckles and yellowish stripes; legs light yellow to brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1438,256,1126]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis box="[199,283,926,950]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[299,400,926,950]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">paratype</typeStatus>
, UBC-SEM AR00078). Carapace length 2.8 (variation 2.8–3.1, n=5); abdomen length 4.9. Chelicera (
